==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glee
<hw>Glee</hw> <pr>(gl⟦emac⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>gle</ets>, <ets>gleo</ets>, AS. <ets>gle⟦oacute⟧w</ets>,
<ets>gle⟦oacute⟧</ets>, akin to Icel. <ets>gl⟦ymac⟧</ets>: cf. Gr. <?/
joke, jest.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Music; minstrelsy; entertainment.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Joy; merriment; mirth; gayety; paricularly, the
mirth enjoyed at a feast.</def> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>An unaccompanied part song for
three or more solo voices. It is not necessarily gleesome.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glee club</ent>⟦br⟧
